# CARL Cold Call Domain
# ======================
# Triggers when Oliver mentions phone prospecting, cold calls, or call scripts.
# Loads call frameworks, pre-call research, and objection handling.
# Compacted 2026-03-19: 8 → 7 rules. Retired meta-description (routing in manifest).
#
# Format: {DOMAIN}_RULE_{N}=rule text

# Step 1: Pre-call research
COLDCALL_RULE_0=Before any call, check brain/prospects/ for existing notes on the contact. Then check Apollo MCP (apollo_contacts_search) for contact data, title, company, stage, and any prior touchpoints. Pull the prospect's LinkedIn profile via web search. The goal: know their name, title, what their company does, and one specific thing to reference on the call.

# Step 2: Load call frameworks
COLDCALL_RULE_1=Read and apply: skills/fanatical-prospecting/SKILL.md (prospecting discipline, call structure, mental toughness), skills/outbound-playbook/SKILL.md (call scripts, objection handling, cadence structure). Also read "docs/Sales Playbooks/sales-methodology.txt" for SPIN and Gap Selling frameworks.

# Step 3: Query NotebookLM for intelligence (tier system: .claude/skills/notebooklm/SKILL.md)
# NotebookLM queries: see brain/notebooklm-queries.md (Cold Call section)

# Step 4: Build the talk track
COLDCALL_RULE_2=Structure the call using Fanatical Prospecting framework: (a) Pattern interrupt — break their autopilot with something specific about their company. (b) Bridge — connect their situation to a relevant pain point. (c) Ask — one question that invites a conversation, not a pitch. Keep it under 30 seconds before the first question. Reference something specific from research — their company, a job posting, their ad library, recent news.

# Step 5: Prepare voicemail script
COLDCALL_RULE_3=If the call goes to voicemail, leave a 15-second max message: Name, company, one specific observation, callback number. Example: "Hi [Name], this is Oliver from Sprites. Noticed [specific thing]. Quick question about it — my number is 555-xxx-xxxx." Do NOT pitch on voicemail. The goal is curiosity, not a sale.

# Step 6: Prepare objection responses
COLDCALL_RULE_4=Have these ready based on Objection Handling notebook data: "Not interested" → "Totally fair. Quick question before I go — [probe]." "Send me an email" → "Happy to. What specifically would be most useful for you to see?" "We already have a solution" → "Got it. Out of curiosity, what are you using? [listen, don't pitch]." "I'm busy" → "I'll be quick — 30 seconds. [bridge to pain point]."

# Step 7: Post-call logging
COLDCALL_RULE_5=After every call, immediately: (a) Update brain prospect note in brain/prospects/[Name] — [Company].md with call outcome, what was said, next steps. (b) Log to Apollo via browser if stage changed. (c) If call went well, feed Objection Handling notebook with any new objections encountered: notebooklm source add "docs/Exports/notebook-feeds/[filename].md" -n 73f909fa-1ebc-4792-aa22-d810df2d7ca0. (d) If demo booked, update brain note with #demo-booked tag and check calendar.
